  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of qt6pas</title>

    <para>
      The <application>qt6pas</application> package is included in
      the <application>Lazarus</application> source package but it
      needs to be built before Lazarus can be built with QT as 
      graphical interface libraries.</para>
    <para>There is no need (no way) to specify the installation 
      target (as usually done by passing --prefix to configure).
      Qt6pas will be installed in QT's library directory. Build the
      package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>cd lcl/interfaces/qt6/cbindings &amp;&amp;
qmake6 "QT += x11extras" &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package does not come with a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, install <application>qt6pas</application> as the
      <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

